---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Is XI a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 9 Points)"
  description="XI is a valid Scrabble word worth 9 points. It's the 14th letter of the Greek alphabet and one of five 2-letter X words. Learn XI strategy and premium plays."
  keywords="is xi a scrabble word, xi scrabble, xi scrabble word, xi points scrabble, two letter x words, greek letters scrabble, x words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Is XI a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 9 Points)",
    "description": "XI is a valid Scrabble word worth 9 points. It's the 14th letter of the Greek alphabet and one of five 2-letter X words.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-23",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-xi-a-scrabble-word" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is XI a valid Scrabble word?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, XI is valid in both the TWL (North American) and SOWPODS (International) Scrabble dictionaries. It scores 9 points (X=8, I=1) and refers to the 14th letter of the Greek alphabet. XI is one of the five valid 2-letter X words." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are all the 2-letter X words in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "There are five valid 2-letter X words in Scrabble: AX (9pts), EX (9pts), OX (9pts), XI (9pts), and XU (9pts). All five score exactly 9 points and are valid in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries. They are essential for X tile management." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do you play XI effectively in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Play XI on premium squares for maximum impact — X on a Triple Letter scores 25 points for just a 2-letter word. XI is especially useful for parallel plays because I is the most common letter on boards. Place XI adjacent to existing words to score in multiple directions simultaneously." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/strategy/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Strategy</a>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is XI a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 9 Points)</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-23">June 23, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Yes, XI is a valid Scrabble word worth 9 points. XI is the 14th letter of the Greek alphabet (Ξ, ξ) and is accepted in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries. It is one of five 2-letter X words and a critical tool for managing the high-value X tile. Because I appears so frequently on boards, XI is often the easiest X word to play.
      </p>

      <!-- Hero Card -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">✓ Valid</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">XI</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">9 points · Greek letter · One of 5 two-letter X words</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">XI is a Greek alphabet letter that serves as one of the most versatile X-tile plays in Scrabble. With I being the second most common tile in the bag, opportunities to play XI appear in nearly every game.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Stat Strip -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Greek Letter</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Definition</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1 of 5</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">2-Letter X Words</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">How to Use XI in Scrabble</h2>

      <p>XI is your emergency X play. When you cannot find a longer word, XI dumps the X tile for 9 guaranteed points — and often much more on premium squares.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Target I-rich zones:</span> I tiles are everywhere on the board. Scan for lone I tiles near premium squares, then slide X next to them for an instant XI. This is especially effective near Triple Letter squares.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel play power:</span> XI placed parallel to a word creates crosswords in both directions. If there is an I adjacent to an open row, XI can score 9 points plus whatever the cross-word produces — often 15-20 total.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Late-game X dump:</span> In the endgame, holding X costs you 8 points if tiles remain. XI is your safety valve — play it immediately rather than risk subtracting X from your final score.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">All 2-Letter X Words Ranked</h2>

      <p>All five 2-letter X words score exactly 9 points, but they differ in playability based on how common their partner letter is.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">XI</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts · easiest</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">AX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">EX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">OX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">XU</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts · hardest</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">XI and AX are the <span class="text-white font-medium">most playable</span> 2-letter X words because I and A are the two most common tiles in the bag (9 each). EX and OX are slightly harder (E has 12 tiles but is used fast; O has 8). XU is hardest since U only has 4 tiles.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Premium Square Scoring</h2>

      <p>XI on premium squares delivers outsized returns for a 2-letter word:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Base Score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">X on DL</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">25</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">X on TL</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">XI on DW</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/all-2-letter-scrabble-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">All 2-Letter Scrabble Words: Complete List for 2026</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-cheat-sheet/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Cheat Sheet: Essential Words & Strategy</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/best-x-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best X Words in Scrabble: High-Scoring Plays</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
